Create collection and create a request to create token, add products to a cart, cart content, edit product quantity in a cart, remove product from a cart.

Create Session/Token
1>Open Postman
2>Create a new collection and name it as Opencart_RestAPI_CartModule
3>Now in the collection variable Tab provide these below details
Ip = your system ip address
baseUrl = http://{{ip}}/opencart/upload/index.php?route=
3>Now create new request and name it as Create Session/Token
4>Now select POST and paste this URL : {{baseUrl}}api/login
5>In the body tab select from-data and enter these below details (Get these details from opencart admin portal)
User name – demo
Key- xxxxx
6>Now in the Post Request paste this code
pm.test("Status code is 200", () => {
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

//capturing response
 var jsonData = pm.response.json();

//Validating JSON response 
pm.test("checking success msg in response", () => {
    pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.eql("Success: API session successfully started!");
   
});

//creating collection variable to store api_token
pm.collectionVariables.set("api_token_val",jsonData.api_token)
Add product to cart
1>create new request under collection and name it as Add product to cart
2>select POST and paste this URL : {{baseUrl}}api/cart/add
3>Now Params add the token which you got in the 1st request
Key : api_token
Value: paste the token
4>Now in the Auth Tab select below details
Auth type : API Key
Key : api_token
Value : {{api_token_val}}
Add to : Query Params
5>Now in the body tab select from-data
Key		type		Value
product_id	text	{{product_id}}
quantity	text 	{{quantity}}
6>Now in the pre-request script add the below code
pm.collectionVariables.set("product_id","40");
pm.collectionVariables.set("quantity","2");
7>now in the post request script add the below code
pm.test("Status code is 200", () => {
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

//Validating JSON response 
pm.test("checking success msg in response", () => {
    var jsonData = pm.response.json();
    pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.eql("Success: You have modified your shopping cart!");
});


