How many ways we can run the collections

1>From the Command Prompt
Pre-requisites:
1.	Install node.js(npm)
2.	Install newman
3.	Export collection

Step 1> we have already installed the node.js just open the command prompt and check if node and npm are installed or not
node -v
npm -v

step 2> Install Newman
npm install -g newman

step 3> export collection
•	select the collection
•	click on 3 dot
•	select export
•	select collection v2.1 and click on Export

how to run the collection from command prompt
Approach 1> Run the collection in the command prompt locally
•	just go the location wherever you have saved your collection
•	In the browser type cmd
•	newman run <enter the collection file name with extension>

now it run the command and display the result.
But if you want to display this result in the HTML format then run the below command

Npm install -g newman-reporter-html

now running the command in the html format
•	just go the location wherever you have saved your collection
•	In the browser type cmd
•	newman run <enter the collection file name with extension> -r html
•	it will generate the report in the same location


Approach 2> Run the collection remotely using URL (other than your computer)
•	Go to postman select the collection
•	Click on 3 dot and click on share
•	Now click on 3 dot share via API
•	Now click on generate new key
•	Copy the URL : https://api.postman.com/collections/46579071-ce1744a1-338f-4a6a-bfa8-56eef44d4068?access_key=xxxxxxxxx
•	Open the command prompt
•	newman run <paste the url> -r html

How to run the collection in jenkins

Approach 3>
1>open the jenkins app
2>login with your credentials
3>Now click on create a new item
4>Given the name as OpenCart_Postaman_Collection
5>Select freestyle project and click on ok
6>now it will navigate to the configuration page for a particular project
7>now come down in the build section and add build step as
Execute windows batch command
8>now paste this below command
newman run <enter the URL which you have create from 2nd approach> 
9>click on Apply and save
10>now it will go the project specific dashboard
11>now click on Build Now
11>you can run this from anywhere just go to home page and select link and click on build now

How to run the collection from the github

Approach 4>
1>login to the github
2>create empty repositories
3>give the name opencart_API_Testing
4>now you will get the repositories url
5>copy that URL

How to create local repositories
1>install git software
2>now go to the location where you have exported the collection
3>right click and open git bash
4>now type
Gir init
5>now type (to connect the local repo with remote repository (github))
Git remote add origin https://github.com/rohitkarekar/opencart_API_testing.git
6>now type (to check the status of file)
git status
7>now type (add the file to index/stage)
Git add Opencart_RestAPI_CartModule.postman_collection.json
8>now type
git status
9>now type (now the file is present in the local repository)
git commit -m “comment”
10>now type (to push the file in the remote repository)
git push origin master
11>now the file is added in the github repository

Now again go jenkins to run the repository
1>open Jenkin
2>New item
3>Opencart_API_github
4>select freestyle project and click ok
5>now select the source code management as git
6>paste the repositories url
7>come to build section select execute windows batch command
8>now paste the below command
newman run <enter the URL which you have create from 2nd approach> 
9>now apply and save
10>click on build now
